rComments: She is amazing, best prof ever!

Very high expectations, with a lot of information taught. The slides can get exhaustive and her explanations often confusing. Her first exam was relatively easy (new prof) but they got progressively harder. 4 assignments, 2 midterms and a final with very demanding material

Overall a good professor. Sometime a bit hard to understand. Always willing to re-explain concepts and willing to spend lots of time doing so. Lots of material to know, but does give lots of hits as to what'll be on the exam.

I feel like the grade I got is not representative at all compared to how much I studied and worked for this class. RIDICULOUS how much details you need to know and her grading is so strict ! She hasn't said the average of the class for the midterms, but I wonder...
She is new and has alot of things to improve about her teaching/grading.

do not take this class with this professor. I was extremely excited about this class until i came to her class. Her expectations are absolutely ridiculous, and her midterms are crazy. She also gives no insight about what will be covered on exams and midterms. Overall, okay for a new prof, but definitely a lot of work to do.

I was pleasantly surprised by her ability to teach since is a first time prof. I find she keeps things simple and clear. There is a nice flow to her lecture and she explains things well. I recommend reading the book, a lot of her slides are form there. We just had out first exam, I found it extremely fair. She seems very relaxed and down to earth.

This professor is new and this term was her first time teaching. I find that she expects her students to learn more details than necessary, so much that it is unrealistic for one midterm. I took this class for the 2nd time to improve my grade and her class is significantly harder than the last professor i had. Doesnt specify her expectations.
